    think='Now I have a good understanding of the PR. Let me compile my review f
indings.\n\nKey issues found:\n\n1. **Major: LoginPage directly triggers SnackBa
r in gesture callbacks** - `login_page.dart` lines ~27-30 and ~39-42 call `Scaff
oldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar()` inside `_onSendCode` and `_onLogin`. Th
e newly added `flutter.md` UI-业务分离 spec explicitly says: "禁止在 `build()` 
或手势回调中直接触发副作用：如 `ScaffoldMessenger.showSnackBar`、`context.go()` 
等应通过 `BlocListener` 响应状态变化后执行." This violates the core purpose of t
he PR.\n\n2. **Minor: Hardcoded animation duration** - `matching_bloc.dart` line
~224 uses `await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 200));` which viola
tes `flutter.md` section "集中式动画时长常量" that says all animation durations 
must use `DesignTokens`.\n\n3. **Minor: Incomplete timer cancellation test** - `
login_cubit_test.dart` line 80-85 tests timer cancellation on close but only ver
ifies `cubit.isClosed`, not that no further emissions occur.\n\n4. **Minor/Note:
The Maestro E2E flow `.maestro/includes/login-as-test-user.yaml` uses `tapOn: "
手机号"` and `tapOn: "验证码"` which rely on labels. The PR added `identifier: \
'login_phone_field\'` and `identifier: \'login_code_field\'` to the SwTextFields
, but the Maestro flow doesn\'t use these IDs. Not a blocking issue since it sti
ll works via label.\n\nWait, looking at the Maestro flow: `- tapOn: "手机号"` - 
this matches the label text. But looking at `flutter.md` Accessibility section:\
n> `# ❌ 错误：通过 label 定位可能匹配到 Text Label，不触发全选`\n\nAnd for Text
Field:\n> `输入框必须暴露 Semantics(identifier: \'xxx\')`\n> `Maestro 通过 tapOn
: { id: \'xxx\' } 精确定位输入框`\n\nThe PR actually **added** identifiers to th
e text fields:\n```dart\nSwTextField(\n  identifier: \'login_phone_field\',\n  .
..\n)\nSwTextField(\n  identifier: \'login_code_field\',\n  ...\n)\n```\n\nThis 
is actually an improvement! The Maestro flow could be updated to use IDs, but th
at\'s not required for this PR.\n\nLet me think about whether there are any Bloc
king issues...\n\nThe LoginPage SnackBar issue is a clear violation of the spec 
that this PR itself introduced. However:\n- It doesn\'t break functionality\n- T
he validation logic IS in the Cubit (the PR did move it)\n- The PR\'s stated sco
pe was M1, M2, M3, M6\n\nLooking at the PR description for M2:\n> - **重构 `Logi
nPage`**：移除所有业务逻辑，仅保留渲染 + 事件转发\n\nThe LoginPage still has `_o
nSendCode` and `_onLogin` methods that do validation-result-to-SnackBar logic. T
his is arguably business logic (deciding to show a SnackBar based on validation 
state).\n\nBut wait - is showing a validation error in a SnackBar "business logi
